6 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 6-101.6b, which relates to whistleblower
7 protection for teachers; making protections
applicable to support employees; defining term;
8 updating statutory references; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-101.6b, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 6-101.6b. A. For purposes of this section, “teacher”
15 means the term as defined in paragraph 1 of Section 1-116 of Title
16 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title, and “support employee” means
17 the term as defined in paragraph 9 of Section 1-116 of this title.
18 B. No school district shall prohibit or take disciplinary
19 action against teachers or support employees for:
20 1. Disclosing public information to correct what the teacher or
21 support employee reasonably believes evidences a violation of the
22 Oklahoma Constitution or law or a rule promulgated pursuant to law;
23 2. Reporting a violation of the Oklahoma Constitution or state
24 or federal law; or
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB508 SFLR Page 1
