1 3. Taking any of the above actions without giving prior notice
2 to the teacher’s or support employee’s supervisor or anyone else in
3 the teacher’s relevant chain of command.
4 C. For the purposes of this section, “reporting” means
5 providing a spoken or written account to a supervising teacher,
6 administrator, school board member, representative from the State
7 Department of Education, law enforcement official, district
8 attorney, and/or parent or legal guardian of a student directly
9 impacted by the actions.
10 D. Each school district shall prominently post or publish a
11 copy of this section of law in locations where it can reasonably be
12 expected to come to the attention of all teachers and support
13 employees.
14 E. Nothing in this section shall be construed to allow a
15 teacher or a support employee to violate students’ or parents’
16 rights to confidentiality and protection under the Family
17 Educational Rights and Privacy Act of 1974 (FERPA).
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
19 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
